race.description: Life Member Mr Bob Howlett Maiden Plate
race.comment: COLONEL BOGEY (2) has been made the favourite in all of his 3 starts this season, most recently finishing fifth over 1200m here 2 weeks ago. This looks like a good chance for him to break through, especially with the blinkers on for the first time. Follow your money. GEEGEES MERCEDES (6) showed speed last start over 1100m at this track and stuck on well for third, finishing just half a length away from the winner. She'll likely go forward again from the wide gate, and could again take some pegging back. JEDD'S JET (8) makes his debut and is by Toorak Toff. He hails from the John Keys yard and will be coming off a placing in a recent Hobart trial. He looks like a strong top-3 contender, especially if the money comes for her. JENNI THE CAT (9) resumes with a recent trial win at Elwick under her belt. She can get worked up pre-race, but can't be risked. ALFARINO (1) is also first-up and shapes as an each-way chance after showing promise at the trials. Let the market be your best guide.
